news.title: Germany’s Aroundtown posts net loss of $2.64 billion in 2023
news.para: On Tuesday the MDax-listed company announced the suspension of its dividend due to market uncertainties and a focus on cash preservation.

news.title: Haryana DC calls meeting over installation of gates in residential societies
news.para: The district administration has received applications from RWAs of several housing colonies in new sectors and other areas of the city citing security problems.

news.title: Indore civic body to auction land worth Rs 23 crore starting March 27
news.para: The bids, with a base price of Rs 31.80 crore, will be opened on Wednesday evening after 5 pm. Experts expect that the market value of the land is significantly higher than the collector's guideline.

news.title: Jaipur civic body issues over 420 notices to urban development tax defaulters
news.para: Janardan Sharma, deputy commissioner (revenue) in JMC Greater, said, “From April 1, 2023 to March 25, 2024, we have collected UD tax of Rs 70.72 crore.

news.title: Delhi: MCD to impose 1% monthly interest on government bodies over property tax dues
news.para: On March 21, MCD’s assessment and collection department issued a circular stating that the interest would be charged if the tax payment was made after the due date June 30 of every financial year.

news.title: Lucknow development body’s vice-chairperson orders removal of illegal encroachments from PMAY buildings
news.para: During the inspection, the LDA V-C found that individuals had occupied the corridors and common areas of the colony with illegal shops and other commercial activities.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body seals 120 commercial properties over tax arrears
news.para: According to GHMC officials, the commercial properties have been sealed after the building owners failed to pay pending arrears in the last two to three years.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body issues notice to PG facility operating from TRP Mall
news.para: Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation officials learned about this after a fire broke out on the mall’s fifth floor on Sunday night, The fire department found out about the facility as they had to rescue its women residents during the fire.

news.title: About 125 housing societies in Pune file water scarcity complaints
news.para: Committee members of housing societies are awaiting a solution to the issue as a meeting has been scheduled with Pune Divisional Commissioner by the end of this week as per directions of Bombay High Court.

news.title: Shriram Housing may see $260 million in inflows post Nifty inclusion
news.para: The highest inflows across all indices are expected from Shriram Housing Finance, HDFC Bank, and Jio Financial Services. The highest outflows are expected to be from SBI, UPL, and ICICI Bank.

news.title: Audit of all under-construction buildings in Kolkata begins
news.para: Once the audit is over, we will submit the list to KMC. The police will collect details from KMC on these buildings and ascertain if they have the necessary sanctions.

news.title: Ghaziabad: NGT orders UPPCB official to appear before it over malls operating without NOCs
news.para: NGT orders UPPCB to address establishments lacking NOCs, fined Rs 1 lakh later waived. Notable entities like Apple Tree Clarks Inn Hotel mentioned. Dr Afroz Ahmad's involvement highlighted. Next hearing on May 9.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency resolution plea against erstwhile promoter of DHFL
news.para: DHFL had availed various term loan facilities of more than Rs 4,000 crore and working capital facilities of Rs 450 crores. Wadhawan had provided unconditional and irrevocable guarantees toward the credit facilities granted by the public sector lender to DHFL.

news.title: Bombay HC approves redevelopment of Mumbai society by Truearth Developers
news.para: It is not an isolated incident, said a division bench of Justices Gautam Patel and Kamal Khata on Thursday. The bench said it sees again and again, a development real estate company under the Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP).

news.title: Prices of under-construction housing properties up 31% in Jan-Mar 2024: Magicbricks
news.para: In its latest PropIndex report, Magicbricks said the demand for under-construction properties increased 7.8 per cent during January-March 2024 from the previous quarter.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong fall by 1.7% in February
news.para: Home prices in one of the world's most expensive property markets dropped 1.7% in February from the previous month, official data showed on Tuesday, following a revised 1.2% fall in January.

news.title: Land prices in Japan rise by 2.3% in 2023
news.para: Average nationwide land prices rose 2.3% in the year through January 1, the strongest pace of growth since a 11.3% gain in 1991 when land prices started weakening with the bursting of the late 1980s asset bubble.

news.title: Australia bank CEOs call for a fix to housing shortage
news.para: At a banking conference in Sydney, the heads of Commonwealth Bank, National Australia Bank and Westpac , Australia's top 3 lenders, blamed a housing supply shortage and urged local governments to speed up planning approvals.

news.title: New home sales in US fall by 0.3% in February 2024
news.para: "Housing activity is stabilizing as homebuilders appear to be building cheaper, and therefore, likely smaller homes," said Conrad DeQuadros, senior economic advisor at Brean Capital.
